<paragraph id="151836E6ED7F321A1755C277CCBAFD3F" blockId="2.[812,1420,193,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">
<emphasis id="27D3EAF4ED7F321A1755C277CCBAFDB0" bold="true" box="[813,974,540,564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Identification.</emphasis>
Thallus laciniate and corticolous, with laminar to marginal ciliary bulbs. Isidia abundant and concolorous, brown to black lower cortex, and presence of nordistic acid in the medulla (K + yellow → orange) (
<bibRefCitation id="71364B17ED7F321A174CC2C8CCB7FD3F" author="Benatti MN" box="[820,963,675,699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref7530" refString="Benatti MN (2012) A review of the genus Bulbothrix Hale: the species with medullary norstictic or protocetraric acids. MycoKeys 2: 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / mycokeys. 2.2522" type="journal article" year="2012">Benatti 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5DBD656DED7F321A1755C2A1CB24FC28" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="151836E6ED7F321A1755C2A1CB24FC28" blockId="2.[812,1420,193,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">
<emphasis id="27D3EAF4ED7F321A1755C2A1CAF8FD65" box="[813,1420,714,738]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" reason="1">
<emphasis id="27D3EAF4ED7F321A1755C2A1CB2EFD66" bold="true" box="[813,1114,714,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D2A74D65ED7F321A101EC2A1CA22FD66" box="[1126,1366,714,738]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Bulbothrix" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis id="27D3EAF4ED7F321A101EC2A1CA22FD66" box="[1126,1366,714,738]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Bulbothrix ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was
</emphasis>
recorded only in the Central Cordillera in 
<collectingRegion id="D763F804ED7F321A1082C287CCE5FCA1" country="Colombia" name="Risaralda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Risaralda department</collectingRegion>
, at between 1500 and 
<quantity id="D25F9B03ED7F321A1004C366CBBEFCA1" box="[1148,1226,781,805]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.725" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" unit="m" value="1725.0">1725 m</quantity>
a.s.l., but its presence is assumed for the rest of the Colombian Andean region (
<bibRefCitation id="71364B17ED7F321A17F9C33BCC83FCED" author="Wolf JHD" box="[897,1015,848,873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" pagination="928 - 960" refId="ref9503" refString="Wolf JHD (1993) Diversity patterns and biomass of epiphytic bryophytes and lichens along an altitudinal gradient in the Northern Andes. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 80 (4): 928 - 960. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2399938" type="journal article" year="1993">Wolf 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="71364B17ED7F321A107DC33BCBBBFCED" author="Bernal R &amp; Gradstein SR &amp; Celis M" box="[1029,1231,848,873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" pagination="1" refId="ref7665" refString="Bernal R, Gradstein SR, Celis M (Eds) (2020) Catalogo de Plantas y Liquenes de Colombia. v. 1. 1. Universidad Nacional de Colombia. Dataset / checklist. https: // doi. org / 10.15472 / 7 avdhn" type="journal article" year="2020">Bernal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In the SNSM it was found on bark in coffee crops in sub-Andean forest between 
<quantity id="D25F9B03ED7F321A17F5C3FFCB6DFC2F" box="[909,1049,916,940]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.575" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.55" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" unit="m" value="1575.0" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="1550.0">1550-1600 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
